node.title: NT's COVID hospitalisations reach new peak of 95, as infected man dies in Tennant Creek
node.alt: NT Health Minister Natasha Fyles speaking at a press conference.
node.description: NT Health Minister Natasha Fyles says aÂ man who was in the "early stages" of a COVID-19 infection has died in Tennant Creek, but his death is not being recorded as COVID related yet.
node.content: ["A man\u00a0with COVID-19 has died in Tennant Creek and the number of coronavirus patients in Northern Territory hospitals has reached\u00a0a new record of 95.", "NT Health Minister Natasha Fyles\u00a0said the man, whose age was unknown,\u00a0died of a cardiac arrest and was in the \"early stages of COVID\".", "\"At this stage, we're not recording this death as a COVID-19 death,\" she said.", "\"But I did think it was important for the public to be aware that sadly this gentleman has passed away.\"", "Of the people in hospital, 15 are receiving oxygen and four are in\u00a0intensive care.\u00a0", "It follows\u00a0the NT recording\u00a0626 new COVID-19 cases in the last reporting period.", "Ms Fyles said 278 cases had been added to Wednesday's case total, bringing the total to 778 \u2013 a new daily record case total for the NT.", "She said the\u00a0number had increased following the processing of extra rapid antigen tests.", "Ms Fyles urged people in the Northern Territory to upload their positive rapid antigen test results as soon as possible onto the NT government's coronavirus website.", "Six new coronavirus cases were recorded in the Alice Springs Correctional Facility, bringing that cluster to 128.", "Ms Fyles said testing rates in Central Australia were not high enough to gain a full understanding of the outbreaks in the region.", "\"So while we are reporting just a handful of cases in communities, we really need people to come forward and get tested so that we can then remain confident we are on top of things,\" she said.", "Ms Fyles said 17 positive cases were recorded from 25 tests conducted in the community of Laramba, west of Alice Springs, yesterday.", "The outbreak in Galiwin'ku on Elcho Island grew\u00a0to 189 after 41 new coronavirus cases were recorded.", "More to come.\u00a0"]
